tips.subject: Full Screen
tips.html:
Full Screen Mode

You can toggle the Eclipse full screen mode via shortcut (Alt+F11) or menu (Window > Appearance > Toggle Full Screen).

tips.subject: Editor List
tips.html:
CTRL+E Editor List

You can quickly switch editors using the Ctrl+E keybinding which opens a list of all open editors. The list supports type-ahead to find the editor as well as allows you to close editors using a popup menu or the Delete key.

tips.subject: Automatic save
tips.html:
Automatic Save

You can configure the automatic save of dirty editors in Eclipse via the General > Editors > Autosave preference page which allows you to enable/disable the autosave and change the interval of autosave.

tips.subject: Start Fresh?
tips.html:
Like to start afresh each session?

A setting on the General > Editors preference page closes all open editors automatically whenever you exit. This makes start-up cleaner and a bit faster.
